Citation.sTitle: Equilibrium Solubility of Sodium 1-Naphthalenesulfonate in Binary NaCl + Water, Na2SO4 + Water, and C2H5OH + Water Solvent Mixtures from (278.15 to 323.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The equilibrium solubility of sodium 1-naphthalenesulfonate in binary NaCl + water, Na2SO4 + water, and C2H5OH + water solvent mixtures was measured by a steady-state method at elevated temperatures from (278.15 to 323.15) K. The results of these data were correlated by a modified Apelblat equation. The dissolution enthalpy (?Hd) and entropy (?Sd) of sodium 1-naphthalenesulfonate in solutions of different mole fraction were obtained.
